parse

public static JsonObject parse(java.io.Reader reader)
                        throws JsonException,
                               java.io.IOException
Creates a JsonObject from a valid JSON string. This routine expects the first non-whitespace character to be '{', then reads a single encoded object from the Reader and leaves the reader positioned after the last '}' character.

Parameters:
reader - Reader positioned to contain a JSON object encoded as a string.
Returns:
a valid JsonObject on success, throws exception on failure.
Throws:
JsonException - The input string is not in valid JSON format.
java.io.IOException - An IO error was encountered before all of the string could be read.
